[In two months a new consignment of plants from Mueller's last journey will arrive, perhaps there will also be seeds in it. The last letter is from the end of May this year, when Dr Mueller was completely recovered from his serious illness.




                        M left for his 'journey into the Australian alps' on 1 November 1854 (M to J. Foster 31 October 1854) and returned to Melbourne on either 8 or 9 March 1855 (M to F. Krichauff, 9 March 1855;M to W. Haines,10 March 1855).M mentionedin both these lettersthat he had had a severe illness, describing it as 'gastrischem Fieber' [gastric fever].

               ]
